#import "/_lib/0.1.1.typ": *
#show: template

#taxon[Idea]
// #title[Title]

A scheme should have property $P$ if its structure morphism has property $P$.
This is part of the philosophy, that we should understand objects of a category
by their interaction with other objects via morphisms. This principle will
*not* hold for all properties of schemes that we define.
